#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:4
msgid "Floating point error handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:8
msgid ""
"Error handling settings are stored in :py:mod:`python:contextvars` allowing "
"different threads or async tasks to have independent configurations. For "
"more information, see :ref:`thread_safety`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:15
msgid "How numpy handles numerical exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:17
msgid ""
"The default is to ``'warn'`` for ``invalid``, ``divide``, and ``overflow`` "
"and ``'ignore'`` for ``underflow``.  But this can be changed, and it can be "
"set individually for different kinds of exceptions. The different behaviors "
"are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:22
msgid "``'ignore'`` : Take no action when the exception occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:23
msgid ""
"``'warn'``   : Print a :py:exc:`RuntimeWarning` (via the Python :py:mod:"
"`warnings` module)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:24
msgid "``'raise'``  : Raise a :py:exc:`FloatingPointError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:25
msgid "``'call'``   : Call a specified function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:26
msgid "``'print'``  : Print a warning directly to ``stdout``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:27
msgid "``'log'``    : Record error in a Log object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:29
msgid "These behaviors can be set for all kinds of errors or specific ones:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:31
msgid "``all``       : apply to all numeric exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:32
msgid "``invalid``   : when NaNs are generated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:33
msgid "``divide``    : divide by zero (for integers as well!)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:34
msgid "``overflow``  : floating point overflows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:35
msgid "``underflow`` : floating point underflows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:37
msgid "Note that integer divide-by-zero is handled by the same machinery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:39
msgid ""
"The error handling mode can be configured :func:`numpy.errstate` context "
"manager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:43
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:47
msgid ""
">>> with np.errstate(all='warn'):\n"
"...     np.zeros(5, dtype=np.float32) / 0.0\n"
"<python-input-1>:2: RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in divide\n"
"array([nan, nan, nan, nan, nan], dtype=float32)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:54
msgid ""
">>> with np.errstate(under='ignore'):\n"
"...     np.array([1.e-100])**10\n"
"array([0.])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:60
msgid ""
">>> with np.errstate(invalid='raise'):\n"
"...     np.sqrt(np.array([-1.]))\n"
"...\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  File \"<python-input-1>\", line 2, in <module>\n"
"    np.sqrt(np.array([-1.]))\n"
"    ~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n"
"FloatingPointError: invalid value encountered in sqrt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:71
msgid ""
">>> def errorhandler(errstr, errflag):\n"
"...     print(\"saw stupid error!\")\n"
">>> with np.errstate(call=errorhandler, all='call'):\n"
"...     np.zeros(5, dtype=np.int32) / 0\n"
"saw stupid error!\n"
"array([nan, nan, nan, nan, nan])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.err.rst:79
msgid "Setting and getting error handling"
msgstr ""

